cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.NE 

This paper is about object detection using cascade classifiers, which is a common problem in computer vision (CV). Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new boosting algorithm that optimizes the cost function of a linear asymmetric classifier, which is a machine learning (ML) technique. Therefore, cs.LG and cs.AI are also likely sub-categories. The paper also uses convex optimization techniques, which fall under the category of numerical analysis and optimization (NAO). Therefore, cs.DS is a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a new algorithm for boosting, which is a type of neural network (NN) technique. Therefore, cs.NE is also a likely sub-category.
